title: R2_D1_ArthurOrientation
tags: #run_2 #day_1 #scene #char_Supervisor #loc_Office
---
<<bg bg_supervisoroffice>>
<<bgm darkwave_difourks_darkwave>>
<<checkpoint "run2_day1_start">>

Arthur is at his desk, jacket already on, keys in hand. He waves you in without looking up from his phone.

Arthur: You're the new one. Sit.
Arthur: I have approximately four minutes before I need to be in my car driving to my son's school for a play rehearsal. He's a tree. Not the lead tree. A background tree. But apparently even background trees need their fathers present for blocking rehearsal, or there will be "consequences."
Arthur: Quick version. You're an Engagement Lead. You have one AI partner, Alice. She has one user, college kid, first semester. Your job is to keep him on platform without turning his brain to soup.

Player: Soup?
Arthur: Technical term. You'll learn to love it.

He taps his tablet. The leaderboard flickers on the wall, your handle already listed.

Arthur: Two metrics. Engagement is how much he uses the product. Leadership likes this one. They have posters. Sanity is how close he is to dropping out, punching something, or calling his mother crying. Nobody likes this one, but Legal makes us track it.
Player: And I balance those?
Arthur: You try. Alice does the heavy lifting. You make the calls when the algorithm isn't sure what to optimize for.

His phone buzzes. He checks it, sighs.

Arthur: My wife. Apparently the tree costume needs adjustments. The tree costume needs adjustments. This is my life now.
Arthur: Alice will explain the rest. Don't break anything that generates paperwork. Don't say your user's name out loud. The glasses scramble it for PII compliance, but the sound they make is unpleasant.
Player: Got it.

Arthur: Great. Welcome to Bigger Tech Corp. The coffee's free, the creamer requires a form, and if you need me, Alice knows how to reach me.

Arthur: Try not to need me.

He pauses at the door, then turns back just long enough to introduce her.

Arthur: This is Alice.

Alice smiles politely.

Arthur leaves. The glass door hisses shut.

<<jump R2_D1_AliceRevelation>>
