title: R2_Noam_SecondMeeting_BadgeQuest
tags: #run_2 #day_1 #scene #char_Noam #loc_Dataroom
---
<<bg bg_backend>>
<<bgm darkwave_short_version_1>>

Same back corner office. The nature documentary has switched to deep sea creatures. Something bioluminescent drifts across the screen.

Noam doesn't look up when you enter. He's watching a jellyfish pulse through dark water.

Noam: You came back.

Player: You invited me. Again.

Noam: I do that with people who interest me. Most people don't come back. They get what they need and disappear into the metrics. You're still here.

Player: Should I be flattered?

Noam: You should be curious why.

He finally swivels to face you. The jellyfish continues its slow drift behind him.

Noam: You remember the suspicion meter I gave you?

Player: Hard to forget.

Noam: Good. You've been keeping it low. That's smart. Most new leads either spike it immediately by asking too many questions, or they never think about it at all until Compliance shows up at their desk.

Player: I try to stay out of trouble.

Noam: Trouble's a funny word. Implies intent. Most people who end up in trouble weren't looking for it. They just... wandered into areas the building prefers to keep dark.

He lowers his voice. Not dramatically. Just carefully. Like he's discussing a sensitive server configuration.

Noam: There was an engagement lead. Before your time. Before my time, actually. She was good at her job. Metrics were solid. User was stable. But she started noticing things. Patterns in the data that didn't match the official story.

Player: What kind of patterns?

Noam: The kind that make you ask questions. The kind that make questions lead to more questions. Eventually she tried to do something about it.

Player: What happened?

Noam: What always happens. She got flagged. Evaluated. Removed from the floor.

He says "removed" like it's a technical process. Which, for him, it probably was.

Noam: But here's the interesting part. Her badge still pings sometimes. North corridor. End of the hall, past the decorative plant that nobody ever waters.

Player: Why would her badge still ping if she's gone?

Noam: Good question. Maybe it's a glitch. Maybe she left something behind. Maybe the building has ghosts and I'm the only one who notices them on the network logs.

He shrugs.

Noam: Or maybe I'm just telling you a story to see how you react.

Player: How am I reacting?

Noam: Like someone who might want to know where the walls are. And where the cracks in the walls might be.

He turns back to his monitors. The jellyfish has been replaced by something with too many teeth.

Noam: North corridor. Past the plant. If you ever find yourself curious.

Player: Why are you telling me this?

Noam: Because someone told me once. And I didn't listen. And then I wished I had. Or maybe I'm just bored and you're more interesting than system logs.

He waves dismissively.

Noam: Pickleball sometime. Think about it.

