title: R2_Dina_SecondMeeting_MailroomQuest
tags: #run_2 #day_1 #scene #char_Dina #loc_Breakroom
---
<<bg bg_breakroom>>
<<bgm darkwave_short_version_1>>

Same break room. Same vending machine. Dina's sitting at the table with a cup of coffee that's clearly been there a while. She's not drinking it. She's waiting.

Dina: There you are. I was starting to think you'd forgotten about me.

Player: I didn't know we had plans.

Dina: We didn't. I just had a feeling you'd show up.

Player: That's either intuition or surveillance.

Dina: In this building, what's the difference?

She pushes a chair out with her foot. An invitation.

Dina: Sit. I need a favor.

You sit. Dina reaches under the table and produces a package. Brown paper, excessive tape, roughly the size and weight of a brick.

Player: What's that?

Dina: A delivery. I need you to take it to the mailroom.

Player: You need me to deliver your mail?

Dina: I need you to deliver my mail to Gus specifically. Tell him it's from me.

Player: Who's Gus?

Dina: Mailroom guy. Been here longer than the building. Knows every package that goes in and out of this place. Knows when people are lying about what's in the boxes. Knows which shipments get extra scrutiny and which ones slide through.

Player: That sounds useful.

Dina: Gus is very useful. Gus also owes me a favor from an incident we don't discuss. This delivery settles part of that debt.

Player: What's in it?

Dina: Firewood.

